<p style="padding:0px 20px 0px 40px;">A member should utilize Club Units from 2015 before end of December 2016 – i.e. two year window period 1/1/2015 – end 2016. A reservation cannot be confirmed in 2016 for occupation in the following year to avoid forfeiting 2015 Club Units.</p>
<p style="padding:0px 20px 0px 40px;">PLEASE NOTE: The above information is provided on the assumption that the member is not in default of the terms and conditions of the Agreement.</p>

<div style="background-color:#b8b8b8; color:white; padding:20px; font-size:22px; margin-left:20px; line-height:150%;">What happens if I still have unused Club Units and I am unable to use them before they expire?</div>
<p style="padding:0px 20px 0px 40px;">You may use your Club Units to make a reservation with QVC, then once your reservation has been confirmed with QVC, you can deposit ("space bank") your week with Dial An Exchange in exchange for a credit on their system, which can be used at a later stage. This enables you to utilize that Credit at an available resort of your own choice through Dial An Exchange. Your 'space banked' week credit with Dial An Exchange is valid for up to three years. A reasonable exchange fee is payable when you do an exchange with RCI or Dial An Exchange. Please note that only QVC Club Stock can be "Space Banked" or exchanged with Dial An Exchange. No RCI stock, even if booked through QVC, will be accepted by Dial An Exchange.</p>
<p style="padding:0px 20px 0px 40px;">Alternatively, you may use your Club Units to make a reservation with QVC, then once your reservation has been confirmed with QVC, you can rent out the confirmed week via <a href="http://www.tradeunipoint.com/home.seam" class="purpleLinks" target="_blank">www.tradeunipoint.com.</a> You can register for free at <a href="http://www.tradeunipoint.com/home.seam" class="purpleLinks" target="_blank">www.tradeunipoint.com.</a> Once you are registered you may deposit the week into the rental pool. The rental amount (less 20%) will be payable to you once the deposited week has been booked.</p>
